  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6598.33 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-16.7B) and positive gamma peak at 6605 (+21.7B), dealers are in active hedging mode within an extremely tight 15-point range. The PIN regime suggests dealers will sell any push toward 6605 and aggressively buy any dip toward 6590, creating strong two-way flow that should keep price pinned in this narrow band. The massive GEX surge (3908% in 1-min) indicates heavy options flow just hit, likely from expiration positioning, making these levels even more critical for dealer delta hedging.\n\nWatch for rejection at 6605 where dealers turn sellers, and strong support at 6590 where they become forced buyers - any break of 6590 opens the door to acceleration toward the next negative gamma wall at 6580.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect tight range-bound trading between 6590-6605 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
